name: 90 Minute Seattle City Highlights Tour
description: Get a quick overview of Seattle’s greatest hits in just 1.5-hours, this sampler small group tour will provide you with insightful information on how to best spend your time exploring Seattle. Listen to the local guide’s colorful stories that keep you entertained and informed along with great local dining recommendations, and lots of other useful information to help you get the most out of your time in Seattle. You should take this tour at the beginning of your visit to benefit from all the great information and recommendations. Choose from one of three departure times when you book.

review.name: Made Seattle fun!!
review.reviewBody: I highly recommend experiencing Seattle with these amazing people! Learned a lot and made my exploring fun and a breeze.

itemListElement.name: Sunset Sail aboard our classic 1926 Schooner

name: Sunset Sail aboard our classic 1926 Schooner
description:
Step back in history aboard the historic Lavengro, a 1926 wooden gaff rigged schooner.  A great boat for experiencing what sailing was like in the last century. This is a great excursion for a romantic evening or the whole family.

Watch seaplane take-offs and landings up close and see the iconic Space Needle, Gas Works Park, the Fremont Bridge, and St. Marks Cathedral. Cruise past dozens of floating homes including the 'Sleepless in Seattle' floating home. See hundreds of boats from classic cruisers to modern mega yachts.

This is a 1.5-hour shared experience with a limited capacity of 22 guests. There is plenty of space on the boat to spread out and enjoy the view, or hop in with your captain and crew to learn how to sail this historic vessel.

review.name: Beautiful Boat but Lousy Experience
review.reviewBody: The description of the trip stated we would be seeing several sights around Lake Union, including Gasworks Park and the Aurora Bridge. However, all we did was sail in circles around the south end of the lake, seeing the same things over and over again. It got boring fast. I’m just glad we didn’t pay money for this as it was a gift. I would not recommend this trip.

name: Market to Table Cooking Class
description: This class takes place in the luxury SieMatic Seattle kitchen studio located in Belltown. This experience starts off with the Chef Owner, Liz McCune, taking you through Pike Place Market to grab seasonal ingredients for the meal. The group will culminate in the SieMatic to cook a three course meal together. The class format is a hybrid between demonstration and hands-on to get the maximum value of the teachings. The experience includes snacks and a three course meal.

name: Ba Bar U-Village
description: Specialties Ba Bar is the place for authentic Vietnamese cuisine in Seattle. We use the highest quality ingredients to create the best Pho in town. We also have one of the top selections of high end spirits on Capitol Hill and we make a great Moscow Mule to boot. Bonus - we serve food until 1:30am on weeknights and 3:30am on weekends. History Established in 2011. Sophie and Eric Banh grew up together eating street food in Saigon, and that was really the inspiration for Ba Bar. When they first opened Monsoon Seattle in 1999, they drew much of their inspiration from the very same "street food" we are serving. With Ba Bar we're just a little closer to the street. But yeah, same owners. Same chefs. Same commitment to quality. And did you know, Ba means father and number 3 in Vietnamese?

itemListElement.name: Mt St Helens Full Day Trip

name: Mt St Helens Full Day Trip
description: You'll see the devastation caused by the 1980 eruption and the slow return of nature’s flora. A full day of sightseeing, you'll visit the Forest Learning Center, and stop for lots of photo opportunities. You'll visit Coldwater Lake and see Castle Lake viewpoint. Johnston Ridge visitors center is closed until 2026 due to flooding that washed out the last bit of road to the visitor center.

review.name: Mt. St. Helen's tour
review.reviewBody: Cheryl was an excellent tour guide.  Her knowledge of the area was superb!  Very friendly and willing to go that extra mile for her customers.  This tour was EVERYTHING we hoped it would be.  Thank you, Cheryl!!!

review.name: super tour
review.reviewBody: What a great tour led by experienced guides.  Was enjoyed by all aboard.  Have been on this tour seveeral times and always the same.

review.name: Wonderful day out
review.reviewBody: Janet was delightful, it was like a personal friend took us out to see Mt St Helens. Very easy to coordinate, Janet picked us up from our Hotel in Seattle and drove us to teh Park. The visitor Centers were very informative and Janet herself was a wealth of knowledge. Had the Volcano Burger for lunch , which was actually quite spicy! My wife Monica and I had a wonderful time, Highly recommend!!

review.name: Great Tour - Wonderful Day
review.reviewBody:
Cheryl is awesome!  
I tried booking a group tour with another company, but it was all booked, and we only had this day available to tour Mt. St. Helens.  This definitely worked in our favor.  We paid a little more for a private tour, but Cheryl made it all worthwhile.  She picked us up at our hotel in a very nice and comfortable SUV.  She had water and snacks available for us.  Cheryl is knowledgeable about the Seattle area and shared many insights and facts as we drove to Mt. St. Helens.  We made a few stops along the way to enjoy sites, gift shops, visitors center, and lunch at a quaint little restaurant on the Toutle River.  Cheryl provided lots of information about the area, Mt. St. Helen's and the eruption of 1980.  Since this was a private tour, Cheryl asked our input on what we'd like to see and do.  We were never rushed, but she also kept things moving, so we could see all we wanted to see and experience.  I highly recommend taking a tour with Cheryl's Northwest Tour company.

itemListElement.name: Private Cascade Mountains and Waterfalls Tour from Seattle

name: Private Cascade Mountains and Waterfalls Tour from Seattle
description: See two fantastic waterfalls both within feet from the parking area, and a fun touristy Bavarian village where you will have lunch on your own. YOU CAN CUSTOMIZE this tour to take out Leavenworth and add in a 2 hour low moderate trail in the cascade foothills in the Snoqualmie area.

review.name: Great experience.
review.reviewBody:
Our tour guide was fantastic! 
Lyle was very knowledgeable and gave us a personalized tour that we really appreciated as a family. 
We enjoyed more sights than we’re advertised because she payed close attention to our interests. 
She even took us to a sight where they filmed Harry and the Henderson’s (: 
What a cool experience. Thanks!

review.name: Wonderful Tour
review.reviewBody: Cheryl was our driver and guide and she was fantastic - very knowledgeable and easy to talk to. The tour was absolutely wonderful - magnificent scenery of mountains and waterfalls, and lunch at the very quaint and interesting little Bavarian town of Leavenworth. Cheryl was very adaptive and made it a great day for us.

review.name: Waterfalls and Cascade Mountain Tour with Cheryl Northwest Tours
review.reviewBody: Fantastic tour!  Highly recommend!  Nicki was the best.  Be sure to ask her about 59er Diner milkshakes!

review.name: Friendly knowledgeable and fun!
review.reviewBody:
Before my trip to Seattle I reached out to Cheryl and talked about her tours. As a photographer wanted to get in as much as I could. She was great to talk with and I booked the Waterfalls, Mountains and Bavaria Tour. 

Janet our tour guide called me the day prior and went over the tour, time she was picking me up and what the weather was going to be like. Something that previous tours never have done. 

Janet made the trip fun, educational and allowed me as a photographer to explore within reason. 

The one thing I would point out about the tour that was disappointing is that we stopped to use the restroom and it was the same place we saw Bridal Veil Falls. But the falls was miles away and if it wasn't for my telephoto lens, I wouldn't have captured a tight photo. I believed we were going up to the falls and not seeing from miles away. 

None the less, it was a great company, great views, great conversation and great sights to be seen.
